This week marked my first real hands on week with Lucidity. With goals clearly set, I worked further on researching and documenting API access requirements and goals. I found some API platforms to be very high maintenance, such as LinkedIn, which led to some priorities being changed as our resources would be better spent on other platforms. By the end of the week, we had a developer email created, partnership accounts set up, and a developer app request sent out for review. Now that the process has started, future applications will be much quicker, and I can begin building the backend architecture to handle the platforms during review.
